{"iteration":8,"focus":"V8 Migration compatibility","newInfoRatio":0.08,"findings":[{"id":"V8-F1","severity":"P1","summary":"Producer behavior for freshness='stale' is not explicit, so an existing session could still emit output from a stale skill graph.","citations":["research/020-pt-02/research-extended.md §X7","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §5 Acceptance Scenario 2","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/004-advisor-brief-producer-cache-policy/spec.md §4.1 REQ-001","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/004-advisor-brief-producer-cache-policy/spec.md §4.1 REQ-007"]},{"id":"V8-F2","severity":"P1","summary":"Generation-counter corruption recovery is not explicit; the spec covers missing/read-only cases but not malformed persisted state during migration bootstrap.","citations":["020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §4.1 REQ-003","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §4.1 REQ-011","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §6 Risks","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md L2 EDGE CASES"]},{"id":"V8-F3","severity":"P2","summary":"The edit -> stale -> rebuild -> generation+1 -> cache-miss sequence is only implied across 003 and 004, not written as one migration scenario.","citations":["020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §5 Acceptance Scenario 2","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §5 Acceptance Scenario 6","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/003-advisor-freshness-and-source-cache/spec.md §5 Acceptance Scenario 8","020-skill-advisor-hook-surface/004-advisor-brief-producer-cache-policy/spec.md §5 Acceptance Scenario 4"]},{"id":"V8-F4","severity":"P2","summary":"First-run bootstrap is mostly covered by composition, but there is no explicit migration acceptance scenario for empty cache plus generation boo